{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 3178736, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wanderingfox", "body": "He's soloable on LFR as long as you're a pet class. Did it pretty easily as an Unholy DK. Just sick your pet on him, stay behind aggramar, and keep healing your ghoul with the crucible of flames essence.\n\nI suspect this would work with any pet class that can heal their pet (hunter etc)", "date": "2019-12-28T08:51:20-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "but how can you do it solo on lfr? since lfr is with more people.. or am i missing something :P", "creationdate": "2020-01-20T16:18:53-06:00", "id": 1349348, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3178736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "silmarilla", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "LFR tiers from previous expansions have an NPC that lets you enter with just your group.", "creationdate": "2020-01-20T20:14:34-06:00", "id": 1349426, "rating": 2, "commentid": 3178736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Underscore4", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Marksmanship Hunter here. I don't know why but he didn't respond to the Growl taunt from my pet, and the only way I got the pet to eat the 3(!) Flame Rends was by doing Feign Death (did it just as he started casting Flame Rend) and he swapped to the pet, which basically seemed to take zero damage from them.", "creationdate": "2020-07-13T07:35:11-05:00", "id": 1379042, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3178736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Ancaglon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "where is the npc to start the LFR? Thank you", "creationdate": "2020-09-18T09:27:43-05:00", "id": 1390651, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3178736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "maxijn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can just go beast mastery and nuke him down without even thinking about Flame Rend because your pet has aggro permanently. Even at level 50 this is trivial as a BM hunter.", "creationdate": "2020-11-30T07:57:26-06:00", "id": 1415337, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3178736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jacevandever", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2019-12-28T08:52:04-06:00", 1, "Wanderingfox"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 3197644, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "hejiann", "body": "I solo'd the LFR version of this on my arcane mage last night and thought I'd share how. Flame Rend is pretty awful\u2013 it's a knockback that, if you're the only one there, is impossible to dodge and will immediately wipe you as it shoots you right off the platform. Aggramar turns to wherever you are when he casts it, and he can cast it multiple times in a row.\r\n\r\nHow I got through that particular ability was by using Blink and Mirror Image, and trying to kill him as fast as possible while ignoring all other mechanics/damage (120 with 440 ilevel, ymmv). On my successful attempt this is what happened:\r\n\r\nFirst, I blew as much DPS as I possibly could in the very beginning of the fight and he didn't cast Flame Rend at all. (On other attempts he did cast it in the first phase so again, ymmv.) It was after he summoned the flame adds that he finally cast Flame Rend and as soon as I went flying I Blinked and was back on the platform. Then he cast it right away again and I cast Mirror Image and got away from his front as fast as I could and just kept DPSing him down. And then he cast it [i]again[/i] but the Mirror Images were still up. Blink is great but it has a 15 second cooldown and I don't know how many times Aggramar can cast Flame Rend in a row but it's at least three. The Mirror Images though do not get knocked off the platform and will hold his attention. For me they held his attention just long enough for me to kill him and get through the encounter. I hope that helps someone else.", "date": "2020-04-03T07:21:43-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 3198228, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Danaan", "body": "In order to not get knocked off the plattform in LFR, you either have to be a pet class (as already mentioned) or must have a minimum DPS of ~50k.\r\n\r\nThe reason for that is: He gains 3 energy every second. When his energy bar is full he uses [url=https://www.wowhead.com/spell=244688/taeshalach-technique]Taeshalach Technique[/url]. If you get him to ~50% before he uses his ability, the energy bar will reset and you have another ~30 seconds to kill him.", "date": "2020-04-06T20:32:54-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You don't need that much dps, I did it on balance druid with 30k dps. I popped my cd at start to bring him down to 60% to start the add phase I killed all the small adds and left two big ones alive untill I had my cds back. After that I was able to kill him with 15 sec to spare.", "creationdate": "2020-05-13T11:57:31-05:00", "id": 1368635, "rating": 9, "commentid": 3198228, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 16384, "username": "cvrky", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Adding on to cvrky's comment: I just solo'd this on my 451 ilvl Ret Pally by doing the same thing cvrky describes - using burst CD's on open then once he's under 60% and spawns the mobs I kept the big ones alive until my CD's were ready again. I then killed the 2 large mobs and popped CD's again, continuing and finishing the fight. I was outputting around 31k dps and was able to successfully solo with his energy not surpassing 60%. Therefore I could avoid being killed by [url=spell=244033]Flame Rend[/url].", "creationdate": "2020-09-28T11:21:41-05:00", "id": 1392829, "rating": 2, "commentid": 3198228, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dylbob", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Or just be death knight. Death's Advance makes you immune to knockbacks.", "creationdate": "2021-03-02T05:01:09-06:00", "id": 1455525, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3198228, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rudy199", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 3220827, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "cheinii", "body": "Monks, mage, lock, dk, hunt, illidari, warr, rogue, paladin and druids can solo him; velfs as well. (rf)\n\nanddddd this evening, i was playing as priest.. xd it was a matter of corruption procs really\n\njust remember to take drums from the ah! he phases at 60%", "date": "2020-08-02T18:31:02-05:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2020-08-02T18:31:43-05:00", 1, "cheinii"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 3252289, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "George14", "body": "Unholy Death Knights can deal with the Flame Rend mechanic by having their ghoul attack Aggramar and hold his attention, and heal your Ghoul with Death Coil. Just stand and watch your Ghoul, use Apocalypse and Army of the Dead when they are up, if Aggramar is about to aggro you, stop attacking and wait.", "date": "2020-11-23T09:31:54-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Still very easy to do at level 50 (don't have Shadowlands yet). With just one resounding protection azerite trait, I only took a tiny couple of percent damage when the two big adds got close. It only took a few minutes, but it wasn't even as long as I thought it would be when I read about this strat.", "creationdate": "2020-11-30T07:56:32-06:00", "id": 1415335, "rating": 0, "commentid": 3252289, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jacevandever", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2020-11-23T09:32:05-06:00", 1, "George14"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 3266144, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hyrcyne", "body": "Just soloed this boss on Mythic on as BM hunter. It might be possible for other pet classes, my BM is surely the best for it.\n\nTalents: 2 - 2 - 1 - 2 - 2 - 1 - 1\nThis isn't necessarily the best setup, it's just what I had when I entered the raid (which I did as MM at first). [spell=193532] and [spell=270581] could've been safer choices.\nCovenant: Venthyr (shouldn't matter which).\nGear: ilvl 178, minimal enchants, [item=158075 bonus=4932:4933:4935] (at level 95) with rank 3 essences - because yes, the HoA and essences still work outside of Shadowlands.\nAlso used the threat bar provided by ElvUI. Threat is very important on this fight because you want your pet tanking the boss at all times.\nI used a [pet=45] because of their [spell=264663] and [spell=264667], though any Ferocity pet should do the job.\n\nI used [spell=264667] right on pull with [spell=34477] on the pet. Watch your threat meters at all times so that you don't take aggro off him. I was slowing down on damage every time I would get close to 40% threat to be safe. Keep using MD on CD so that you can safely cast a few DPS spells in that short window. The whole reason we don't want aggro on us is that Aggramar uses [spell=243431] on any melee attacks and it stacks up really fast. This won't affect your pet however.\n\nTry to stay somewhere behind Aggramar at a far distance so that you don't get knockback off the platform by [spell=247079] when he reaches 100 energy. [i]At the event where this may happen, you might be able to cancel the knockback with [spell=781], although this may be tricky to do.[/i]\n \nDuring the intermissions where the boss goes immune, this is where you need to blow up the two big [npc=121985] adds. Let the small [npc=122532] reach the boss, this will give you one stack of [spell=244912] for each add. This does quite a bit of damage, so make sure you're actively DPSing the big adds so that you leech health off them. If you have a higher DPS than I did, you may want to save them until the small ones reach Aggramar so that you can DPS them instead of the boss for leech (otherwise you might take back the aggro from your pet). No point of saving turtle for the debuff, it will go through it.\n\nJust dodge any other mechanics and the fight should be relatively easy.\n\nIt took me 6:56 minutes, about 2 minutes away from enrage, to solo him. I was doing 20.5k DPS and 358 HPS.\n\nEDIT (much later on!): Was able to duo this boss fairly easily with a Shadow Priest friend, both 220+ ilvl, with me as a MM Night Fae instead of BM Venthyr and no Heart of Azeroth equipped. I kept aggro the whole fight, managed to Disengage the only knockback that happened. Was also able to duo Mythic Argus without any real trouble.", "date": "2020-12-04T03:56:41-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2021-04-19T01:50:05-05:00", 1, "Hyrcyne"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 5252229, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Persophone", "body": "It hasn't been mentioned yet, but this guy IS soloable, so long as you have something that allows you a \"dash\" mechanic, such as Soulshape, through the Night Fae Covenant. Once he starts casting his Flame Rend ability, get ready to hit your Soulshape. Once it allows you to dash through, don't hit him (stay shifted). He'll cast again almost immediately. Dash through, then begin dps'ing him down. He'll cast his Flame Rend ability again, and it should have been enough time for your CD to end, and you can repeat the above maneuver. You should be able to kill him after the second one! Hope this helps some other Pally like me!", "date": "2021-09-11T15:18:30-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}}
